previous recruitment activities.  Please include them when you reach out to students for your graduate programs.  UIC Faculty and staff can also access information on prospective applicants that registered to receive information about UIC graduate programs through the National Name Exchange . To view a complete list of all NNE participants filtered by discipline please click on the Fall 2019 NNE Filtered by Discipline.  You may find participants indicating Fall 2019 or Spring 2020 graduation by selecting the “Grad Year”  filter/tab.  The National McNair Scholars Directory for 2020 may be found here [forthcoming].  Please contact: Lunaire Ford , Assistant Dean, Recruitment & Diversity for more information. Click on the listed individual events to access the corresponding Excel spreadsheets containing student and or event information.  Recruitment Events, Dates and Locations:  Fall 2019  Vanderbilt/ National Name Exchange Feeder Program, September  23-25, 2019 Nashville, TN  National Association of African American Honors Programs – November, 6-9;  New Orleans, LA  Society of the Advancement of Chicanos and Naive Americans (SACNAS) Conference – October 31 – November 2, 2019; Honolulu, HI  American Biomedical Research Conference for Minority Students (ABRCMS) Conference –  November 13-16: Anaheim, CA    Spring 2020  Hampton University – February  Summer 2020  SAEOPP National McNair Conference ,  June – Atlanta, GA  Annual Ronald E. McNair Scholars Symposium at UC Berkeley . July – Berkeley, CA  University of Buffalo McNair Conference , July – Niagara, NY    Fall 2020              Diversity    Back to main content           Recruitment    Fellows Mentoring & Support    DFI Program    PIF Program    PBRC-PREP Program    SROP Undergraduate Program     SROP Early Admissions Fellowship                     UIC Logo         Graduate  College           Campus Resources    Academic Calendar    UIC Today    Event Calendar    UIC Maps    Visit & Directions    Clery Compliance    